Package oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena

This package contains all the logic implementing Jena Graph/Model/DatasetGraph/BulkUpdateHandler APIs and the logic implementing storing and retrieving of SPARQL queries and XSLTs from Oracle database.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DotStringProcessor
    This interface defines APIs so that users can plugin their own processing of RDF data for DOT file generation.
    StatusListener
    To provide customized status change handling, implement this interface.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Attachment
    A class that helps GraphOracleSem and DatasetGraphOracleSem query multiple Oracle RDF/OWL/SKOS models, and/or run inference using specified rulebase(s).
    Constants
    A collection of constants.
    DatasetGraphOracleHybrid
    An extension of DatasetGraphOracleSem class.
    DatasetGraphOracleSem
    An implementation of ARQ's DatasetGraph interface that works with Oracle Database 11g Semantic Technologies.
    Domain  
    DotStringProcessorNoop
    This class provides a no-op implementation of DotStringProcessor interface.
    GraphOracleSem
    An implementation of Jena Graph interface that works with Oracle RDBMS 11g semantic storage.
    GraphStats
    A class responsible for reading some basic graph metrics for an instance of GraphOracleSem.
    InferenceMaintenanceMode
    This class specifies the mode of maintaining rules index (entailment).
    ModelOracleSem
    This class implements the Jena Model API.
    OntologyUtils
    A collection of utility functions for Ontology handling.
    Oracle
    This class manages the RDBMS JDBC connection to an Oracle semantic store.
    OracleBulkUpdateHandler
    An Oracle specific implementation of Jena BulkUpdateHandler API.
    OracleCapabilities
    An Oracle-specific implementation of the Capabilities interface.
    OracleGraphBase
    An internal common graph parent class.
    OracleGraphWrapperForOntModel
    Represents a graph backed by an Oracle RDF/OWL/SKOS model in an Oracle semantic store that is meant to be used in conjunction with Jena's OntModel.
    OracleModelBase
    This class holds general information about the underlying Oracle models used by Oracle model implementations.
    OracleNamedGraph
    Represents a named graph backed by an Oracle Semantic Technologies model.
    OraclePool
    This class is a wrapper of OracleDataSource.
    OraclePrefixMapping
    A PrefixMapping implementation that synchronizes its state with an Oracle database table.
    OracleQueryMgtServlet
    Servlet Entry point to Oracle SPARQL Query Management.
    OracleQueryProgressMonitor
    This class implements logic to manage query executions.
    OracleSemIterator
    This class extends NiceIterator.
    OracleSemIterator.ValueInfo  
    OracleSemQueryHandler
    This class extends SimpleQueryHandler with functions that utilize Oracle's SQL-based RDF graph pattern match.
    OracleSemQueryPlan
    This class implements BindingQueryPlan by translating a query into a single SDO_RDF_MATCH-based SQL query.
    OracleTransactionHandler
    This class extends the TransactionHandlerBase implementation.
    OracleTranslator
    This class is a helper class that translates between Jena Nodes and the internal representation of values expected by Oracle.
    OracleTripleIterator
    An Oracle specific triple iterator that extends OracleSemIterator.
    OracleUserRule
    This class abstracts out user-defined rules supported by Oracle.
    OracleUserRuleBase
    This class implements a rulebase that corresponds to the Oracle Database 11g Release rulebase design.
    OracleUtils
    A collection of utility functions.
    QueryOptions
    This class allows the user to specify necessary options used by SDO_RDF_MATCH (or SEM_MATCH in 11g) so that queries against an inferred graph with INCOMPLETE or INVALID status can go through.
    SemNetworkAnalyst
    This class provides key network analytical functions on top of semantic data.
    SGConstants
    This class contains some default constants used by SPARQL Gateway.
    SGDBHandler
    This class handles all Database related activities for SPARQL Gateway.
    SimpleLog
    A Simple wrapper of Apache Commons Logging API.
    TripleSource
    A class that serves as a proxy to an instance of Iterator, Array, or List.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ModelOracleSem.OptFlags  
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CannotFindRuleException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the rule to be removed cannot be found in the rulebase.
    CannotReadRulebaseException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the rulebase cannot be read (select) due to insufficient privilege.
    CannotWriteRulebaseException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the rulebase cannot be written (insert/delete/update) due to insufficient privilege.
    ConnectionSetupException
    An exception class that is used to denote error condition during connection setup.
    IllegalQueryPatternException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the query pattern is illegal.
    IncompleteStatusException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the inferred graph has an INCOMPLETE status.
    InvalidStatusException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the inferred graph has an INVALID status.
    NoEntailmentException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the inferred graph does not exist.
    NullConnectionException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the connection retrieved from OraclePool is null.
    RuleAlreadyExistsException
    An exception class that is used to denote that the rule to be added already exists in the rulebase.

Package oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena Description

This package contains all the logic implementing Jena Graph/Model/DatasetGraph/BulkUpdateHandler APIs and the logic implementing storing and retrieving of SPARQL queries and XSLTs from Oracle database.
